    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. NIH predictions satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion at all five operating points including the worst-case condition. The CFD model is deemed sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission decision for the Class II CPB device. Note: aleatory uncertainty in the wall shear stress validation result was acknowledged qualitatively in the test narrative but was not formally characterised through a structured UQ link in the evidence package.",
